      <h1 align="left"><!-- #BeginEditable "title" -->Segment<!-- #EndEditable --></h1>
      <hr>
      <!-- #BeginEditable "main" --> 







      <p><a href="http://www.heiberg.se/segment/download.htm">[Download now]</a></p>







      <p>Segment is a comprehensive free software package for Medical Image Analysis 
        and Cardiac Image Analysis. It is constructed with cardiovascular MRI 
        (CMR) in mind but it has also been validated using Cardiac CT, and tested 
        using myocardial perfusion SPECT. With the general object segmentation 
        module it can be used for a wide range of Radiology and Cardiology applications. 
      </p>







      <p>It is brought to you by <a href="mailto:einar@heiberg.se">Einar Heiberg 







        </a>at the <a href="http://www.med.lu.se/klinvetlund/klinisk_fysiologi/forskning/cardiac_mr_group">Cardiac 







        MR group</a>, at Lund University, and <a href="http://www.medviso.com">Medviso 







        AB</a>.</p>







      <p align="center"><img src="images/main.jpg" width="450" height="322"></p>







      <p>The software is <font color="#FF0000">completly free for non commercial 
        research!</font> All we ask in return is that you <a href="referto.htm"><font color="#FF0000">reference</font></a> 
        the software properly when publishing scientifically. To learn more on 
        how the software can be free for research see the <a href="about.htm">about</a> 
        page. </p>
      <p>Details on commercial use are given <a href="license.htm">here</a>. For 
        <font color="#FF0000">commercial use</font>, such as daily clinical routine 
        or usage from research companies you need a commercial license which is 
        provided by the company <a href="www.medviso.com/order.htm"> Medviso AB</a>. 
        The commercial license is FDA 510(k) approved.</p>







      <p>I hope that you like the software and please send feedback to the Segment 
        development team. We are also open for research cooperation if there would 
        be specific functionality that you are missing.</p>
